Review Content: My visit was for a Final Fantasy Piano Concert and my review is for the setup. First the chairs are placed in a way that if someone taller sits in front of you, good luck at seeing anything. This could be fixed by placing the chairs behind diagonally. Luckily nobody was sitting in front of me but at least 2 of my friends had this problem. Second, and this was annoying me, the center piece is the piano and so the stage light was on it and all I could see was the piano with smudges. Please clean your piano or whatever if it's going to the focus. It was really annoying to see and can't be unseen like the arrow in the FedEx logo.
Owner Response:
Hi Mka. Thank you for you feed back. We are sorry to hear that you had encounter inconveniences during your visit. In this kind of set up we place our chairs in staggered rows, so as to facilitate visibility of the sage for all. But if you have trouble seeing the stage and enjoying the show,  in this situation, we encourage you to go talk to our hall manager or ushers, they would have gladly help you sorting this seatting situation and make sure you had the best experience possible. 
Regarding the piano, we are renting it from the best piano renting place in Montreal and once they have settled it on the stage and tuned it, we can no longer touch it. But we will be sharing your comment to make sure we are according extra attention to those details at any kind of events we have. 
I hope we will have the pleasure to welcome you again at our venue and make sure you have the best experience here. 
Best,
